      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="http://www.morgansmenu.blogspot.com" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Morgansmenu</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2010/12/wade-way-in/#comment-20602"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2010-12-06T01:43:01-05:00">Monday, December 6, 2010 at 1:43 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>This recipe (and others) might also benefit from toasting the flour ever so slightly to really accentuate the nutty flavors.  I once bought a brownie made from acorn flour that had been toasted and he told me that lightly toasting flours in the oven, say around 200 degrees, can make a huge difference.  Try it!</p>
    </div>

